<para id="fs-id1167794200080">For the following exercises, the rectangular coordinates of a point are given. Find two sets of polar coordinates for the point in <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>π</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>]</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> Round to three decimal places.</para>
