</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1167793279600">
<problem id="fs-id1167793279602">
<para id="fs-id1167793279605"><emphasis effect="bold">[T]</emphasis> Use a graphing utility to plot <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>θ</m:mi><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>sin</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mi>θ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> for <m:math><m:mrow><m:mtext>−</m:mtext><m:mi>π</m:mi><m:mo>≤</m:mo><m:mi>θ</m:mi><m:mo>≤</m:mo><m:mi>π</m:mi><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1167793279662">
<problem id="fs-id1167793279665">
<para id="fs-id1167793279667"><emphasis effect="bold">[T]</emphasis> Use technology to plot <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>−0.1</m:mn><m:mi>θ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> for <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−10</m:mn><m:mo>≤</m:mo><m:mi>θ</m:mi><m:mo>≤</m:mo><m:mn>10</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
